mongodb-driver-examples
-----------------------

Introduction at:
http://blog.mongolab.com/2011/11/ample-mongodb-examples/

This git repository includes mongodb connection and query examples
for the following:

    -Java
     http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Java+Language+Center

    -Node.js (using Mongoose)
     http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/node.JS

    -PHP
     http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/PHP+Language+Center

    -Python (using pymongo)
     http://api.mongodb.org/python/current/

    -Ruby (using the official driver from 10gen)
     http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Ruby+Language+Center

    -Ruby (using MongoMapper)
     http://mongomapper.com/documentation/

    -Ruby (using Mongoid)
     http://mongoid.org/en/mongoid/

These examples should run outright after you install the appropriate
drivers and get a MongoDB database running on your localhost. See
http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Quickstart for guidance. If you
are using a remote database, simply replace the example URI with
your own.

Currently, we provide a simple connection with authentication and 
query examples. We are working on expanding to cover
replica set connection and failover. Check back for updates!

We hope these are helpful and appreciate your feedback!

Sincerely,
The MongoLab Team
http://www.mongolab.com
